Phishing Simulation Mini-Range
Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Set up a controlled phishing simulation environment on Linux
Create realistic phishing email and SMS templates
Build credential capture forms with logging mechanisms
Understand technical components of social engineering attacks
Practice ethical security testing in an isolated environment
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command-line skills
HTML/CSS fundamentals
Understanding of HTTP and web servers
Python basics
Lab Environment
Al Nafi provides a Linux-based cloud machine. Click Start Lab to access your system. All tools will be installed during the lab. This is an isolated environment for educational purposes only.

ETHICAL WARNING: This lab teaches defensive security. Never use these techniques against real targets without explicit written authorization.

Task 1: Infrastructure Setup
Step 1.1: Install Core Components
Update system and install required packages:

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y apache2 php mysql-server python3 python3-pip git nano
sudo systemctl start apache2 && sudo systemctl enable apache2
Install Python dependencies:

pip3 install flask requests
Step 1.2: Configure Directory Structure
Set up working directories:

sudo chown -R $USER:$USER /var/www/html
cd /var/www/html
sudo rm -f index.html
mkdir -p phishing/{templates,forms,logs,assets}
cd phishing
Create log directory with proper permissions:

mkdir -p logs
chmod 755 logs
